  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Zero test files exist in this project** (only matches for \"test\" were inside `.venv` site-packages). `requirements.txt` has no test framework. 1,505 lines across 8 modules are completely unverified. Below is the gap analysis per module, in priority order (pure logic → I/O-heavy), with skeletons for each gap.\n\nFirst, add dev dependencies (not currently in `requirements.txt`):\n```\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\nrespx>=0.21        # mock httpx transport for fetchers.py\nfreezegun>=1.5     # freeze datetime.now() for posted_at/cutoff tests\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` — highest value, zero risk to add\n\n**Untested:** `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `Job.posted_dt`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`\n\n**Edge cases missed:**\n- Empty string / `None` input to `parse_posted_at`\n- Millisecond vs second epoch boundary (the `>= 1e12` heuristic — a second-epoch value just under 1e12 vs a ms-epoch value just over)\n- Negative epoch (`lstrip(\"-\")` handling)\n- ISO string without `Z`/offset (naive) vs with `Z` vs with explicit offset\n- Garbage string → must return `None`, not raise\n- `content_hash` stability — same fields → same hash; changed field → different hash\n- `to_row()` must drop `raw` and add `key`/`content_hash`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_and_none_return_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None\n\n    def test_garbage_string_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"not a date\") is None\n\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"epoch,expected_year\", [\n        (\"1643241332430\", 2022),   # ms (13 digits)\n        (\"1643241332\", 2022),      # seconds\n        (\"-100\", 1969),            # negative epoch\n    ])\n    def test_numeric_epoch_variants(self, epoch, expected_year):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(epoch)\n        assert dt.year == expected_year\n        assert dt.tzinfo is not None\n\n    def test_iso_with_trailing_z(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2026-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt == datetime(2026, 1, 15, 10, 0, tzinfo=timezone.utc)\n\n    def test_naive_iso_gets_utc_attached(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2026-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_workday_prose_is_unparseable(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **overrides):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"42\",\n                     title=\"SWE\", url=\"https://x\", location=\"NYC\", department=\"Eng\")\n        base.update(overrides)\n        return Job(**base)\n\n    def test_key_is_stable_across_title_change(self):\n        j1, j2 = self._job(title=\"SWE\"), self._job(title=\"Senior SWE\")\n        assert j1.key == j2.key == \"greenhouse:acme:42\"\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_material_change(self):\n        j1, j2 = self._job(), self._job(title=\"Different Title\")\n        assert j1.content_hash != j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable_for_identical_fields(self):\n        assert self._job().content_hash == self._job().content_hash\n\n    def test_to_row_drops_raw_adds_key_and_hash(self):\n        row = self._job(raw={\"secret\": 1}).to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == \"greenhouse:acme:42\"\n        assert \"content_hash\" in row\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` — pure logic, easy wins, currently zero coverage\n\n**Untested:** `match`, `filter_jobs`, `_compile` (word-boundary regex behavior)\n\n**Edge cases missed:**\n- Include/exclude interaction (exclude wins even if include also matches)\n- Word-boundary matching (`\"go\"` shouldn't match `\"Django\"`)\n- Case-insensitivity\n- Empty rules dict → everything passes\n- `cutoff`