aml\", dry_run=False)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Missing error-handling tests specifically (cross-cutting)\n\n| Location | Untested failure path |\n|---|---|\n| `fetchers._request` | exhausted retries → `RuntimeError`; non-retryable status (404) doesn't retry |\n| `fetchers.fetch_source` | unknown `ats` → `ValueError` |\n| `fetchers.fetch_all` | one source's exception is swallowed and logged, run continues |\n| `fetchers.fetch_meta` | GraphQL response with `errors` key → `RuntimeError` (rotated doc_id case) |\n| `notify.dispatch` | one notifier's exception doesn't stop the rest |\n| `notify.notify_sms` | Twilio error response propagates via `raise_for_status()` |\n| `agent.cmd_db_mark` | invalid watermark / missing args → exit code 2, not a crash |\n| `agent._chrome_bin` | no Chrome found → `sys.exit` with message |\n| `agent.cmd_pdf_render` | missing input file → exit code 2; Chrome subprocess failure → exit code 1 |\n| `models.parse_posted_at` | never raises regardless of input — currently only implicitly guaranteed |\n\n### Integration test gaps\n\n- **End-to-end pipeline**: fetch (mocked HTTP) → filter → store diff → notify, asserting DB state after two consecutive runs (first run all \"new\", second run with one changed title → \"changed\", rest untouched).\n- **`agent.py db-new` → `db-mark` cycle**: run `db-new`, feed its `watermark` into `db-mark`, confirm the next `db-new` doesn't re-surface the same rows and doesn't skip rows written mid-group.\n- **Multi-source `fetch_all` with mixed ATS types**: one Greenhouse + one Lever + one failing Workday in the same config, asserting partial success.\n- **Store migration + diff on a pre-existing legacy DB file** (schema evolution in place, not just fresh `:memory:`).\n\n### Suggested `conftest.py` fixtures to add once tests land\n```python\n# tests/conftest.py\nimport pytest\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    s = Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\")\n    yield s\n    s.cl